Preconditions:
- The input array `points` is not null.
- The length of the input array `points` is greater than or equal to 1.
- The coordinates `x` and `y` of each point in the input array `points` are within the range of -10^6 to 10^6.
- All pairs of coordinates `(x, y)` in the input array `points` are distinct.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the minimum cost to make all points connected.
- All points in the input array `points` are connected.
- There is exactly one simple path between any two points in the input array `points`.